\date{2024-05-29}
\title{monadic adjunction}
\taxon{definition}
\author{rileyshahar}

\import{macros01}
\cite{riehl-2017}{Riehl}{Definition 5.3.1}

\p{An [adjunction](rs-0043) is \em{monadic} if the [comparison functor](rs-004G)
to the [Eilenberg-Moore category](rs-004G) is an [equivalence of
categories](rs-0012). A [functor](rs-000L) #{D\xto{G} C} is \em{monadic} if it
is the left adjoint in a monadic adjunction; in this case #{D} is \em{monadic}
over #{C}.}

